@node Introduction "Introduction"

                                 @{b}Introduction@{ub}

    This  is  a  simple program to check system vectors. There are a lot of
viruses in this vectors. This programs checks vectors all the time.

    With  this program you can check your bootblocks. This program know OFS
and FFS bootblocks and disk whithout installed bootlblock.

@endnode

@node Instructions "Instructions"

                                 @{b}Instructions@{ub}

    You  can run this program from WB and from CLI. If you run program from
CLI you should use Run command.

    If the program start you will see a window. All functions are in menu.

    These are the options:

 - About - information about me and program;

 - About System - information about your system (version MC, memory etc.);

 -  Vectors...  -  with this function you can clear vectors and check their
contents;

 -  BootBlock...  -  you can install the bootlblock and check the bootblock
with this function;

 - Reboot System - this reset your Amiga;

 -   Iconify   -   iconify   the   program   (you   must   have   an   icon
ENV:Sys/def_BlaBla.info);

 - Quit - quit program.

@endnode

@node Requirements "System requirements"

                                 @{b}Requirements@{ub}

    An Amiga with system 2.0+.

@endnode

@node Errors "Error messages"

                                @{b}Error Messages@{ub}

    If you run program from CLI you will see messages in CLI window. If you
run program from WB you will see messages in requesters.

@endnode

@node Instalation "Instalation"

                                 @{b}Instalation@{ub}

    Just copy the drawer with program where ever you want. And copy icon
ENVARC/Sys/def_BlaBla.info to ENVARC:Sys.

@endnode

